{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make additional autism-specific training mandatory for all speech therapists",
        "additional_details": "The new training should focus on ensuring autistic individuals have their specific Speech, Language & Communications needs met & give all Speech Therapists the confidence to recommend, refer & support an autistic individual\u2019s communication needs. This would include augmentative & alternative communication, language processing & understanding of speech disorders such as Apraxia - with a specific focus on how these impact & relate to autistic individuals.\r\n \r\nThis new training could be called \"Speak Up for Autism.\"",
        "background": "I believe Speech Therapy is failing autistic children and that change is long overdue. This campaign calls to make additional autism-specific training mandatory for all prospective & practising NHS Speech Therapists. Please sign this petition today to Speak Up for Autism.",
